&lt;p&gt;from Christopher Torrence and Gil P. Compo&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which use the &lt;strong&gt;NINO3.4&lt;/strong&gt; seasonal time series (The &lt;strong&gt;NINO3.4&lt;/strong&gt; index is calculated as the regional average of Sea - Surface - Temperature (SST) anomalies in the central eastern Pacific [5°N to 5°S, 170°W to 120°W.] and is one of the most used indices for tracking the the El Niño - Southern Oscillation phenomenon)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See also the &lt;a href="http://ion.exelisvis.com/"&gt;Interactive Wavelet page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
